Facilyn: Now we describe how the land and environment must be far into the future to sustain your quality of life. Even if you don't directly manage land, it's important to describe your surroundings, because you will always need air, water, food and so on.

Facilyn: We'll think in terms of the four ecosystem processes: water cycle, mineral cycle, community dynamics, and energy flow.

